item.title: Joshua Gaunya
item.dc:creator: curtis.campbell
item.content:encoded:
A founding partner, Josh Gaunya is Vice President and Director of Operations at deasy penner podley.  As a real estate agent, his focus has been on architectural, design-centric and historical single-family homes and estates. He has represented sellers and buyers of properties from the Hollywood Hills and Sunset Plaza, Beverly Hills to the Westside and beyond.

Additionally, he manages the deasy penner podley multi-unit division â a team dedicated to working with developers, investors and bankers to successfully market and sell several hundred design-centric condominium projects throughout Southern California.

Upon his arrival to Los Angeles, Josh worked as a sales agent for Mossler, Deasy & Doe, a residential real estate firm representing architectural and historic properties throughout Los Angeles.

Prior to real estate, he has worked for Gap Inc. in San Francisco,  overseeing product development & design, marketing, merchandising, planning & distribution. As well as working on the trading floor at Tucker Anthony Investments, a mergers and acquisitions firm in Boston.

Josh graduated, Magna Cum Laude from Northeastern University, with a Bachelor of Science in Business Administration: Finance & Marketing and a minor in Sociology. He has always had a passion for design, which he attributes to working in construction development, beginning at childhood with his family. Josh has a great appreciation for design and culture and spends his free time exploring the urban landscapes of the world.

item.title: Frank Langen
item.dc:creator: curtis.campbell
item.content:encoded:
Email: frank@fakedomain.com

Personal Website: fakedomain.com

Born in Santa Monica, Frank Langen was schooled in both Europe and the United States. He was first drawn to art & architecture in his youth by numerous architectural projects his parents built and visited around the world.

Langen graduated from the University of Colorado at Boulder with a degree in Economics and Philosophy. Soon after he returned to Europe taking a position with Cargill Industries as a commodities trader stationed in Paris, Milan and Hamburg. Eventually Langen practiced photography after apprenticing for several notable photographers.

In 1999 he started the inthecanyon.com website serving the Santa Monica and Rustic canyon areas. Langen currently resides in the canyon successfully selling real estate all over Los Angeles. He bases himself out of his offices at 169 W. Channel Road. The building designed by Jim Tyler also houses his gallery which specializes in photography.

For a comprehensive, cohesive, integrated marketing and communication strategy for selling your home you can reach Frank at 310-963-3891 or frank@fakedomain.com

item.title: Alexis Hilton
item.dc:creator: ray.su
item.content:encoded:
Alexis Hilton: A Real Estate of Affairs

From coast to cost Alexis Hilton has been matching people with their dream spaces for fourteen years. As a New York City native she began her career specializing in Corporate Furnished Rentals. Alexis continuously proved that in a city of 8.6 million there's a perfect fit for everyone.

As a trained actress and singer it is no surprise that Alexis brings total harmony to the process of finding you the ideal home. Living in Europe for five years, Alexis traveled and absorbed the many different styles and influences of European cultures. So, you can trust her when she points out details like the Tuscan design of a window frame or what makes a French door so French. She may even say it in Italian. Alexis is now located in Los Angeles and of course adores it. I mean you get it. You're looking for a place here right now. It's glorious.

Alexis made her mark in Los Angeles as a consistent top performer at a prominent high volume Leasing Agency. She is also the consecutive winner of an award I just made up called "The Always Killing It Awards." The main reason being that she is always killing it! She finds such success by loving what she does and respecting the trust that her clients put in her to discover their new dwelling. Alexis is excited for you to put that trust in her like countless have before and be the first to tell you "Benvenuto a Casa."

item.title: Adriana Donofrio
item.dc:creator: cody.stivanson
item.content:encoded:
Adriana Donofrio has been working with buyers and sellers throughout the San Gabriel Valley and Inland Empire since 1982, specializing in residential and investment properties. She maintains an active clientele who value her knowledge, competence and commitment to personal service. Adriana holds the prestigious CRS designation awarded by the Council of Residential Specialists to fewer than 4% of Realtors nationwide who have completed the rigorous educational requirements & sales experience.

The satisfaction of her clients is of the utmost importance. "Home is where the heart is...and helping people relocate across town or across the country brings a personal satisfaction that is one of the greatest rewards in this business. I am truly grateful for the trust and confidence my customers have shown in allowing me to handle one of life's most important transactions."

Adriana Donofrio was born in New Haven, Connecticut, and her father, an Old World craftsman of fine cabinetry, kindled her interest in home construction. She has lived in the San Gabriel Valley since 1975, currently residing in Claremont with her golden retriever Dino.

item.title: Andrea Barrett
item.dc:creator: zachary.truong
item.content:encoded:
Re-Designing the Real Estate Experience

As a lifelong resident of Sierra Madre, Andrea Barrett serves clients all along the Foothill Communities. Andrea brings a depth of knowledge and experience to her clients along with a passion to make their experience one that they would recommend to their friends and family. Her meticulous attention to detail coupled with warmth and personal skills create the perfect balance for a mutually rewarding experience. As a full time agent, Andrea prides herself on providing each and every client with the focus, discretion, and integrity that her clients have come to appreciate and expect.

Andrea has been in the Real Estate industry since 2008, prior to that she was an Interior Designer for over 23 years, often assisting other Real Estate agents with staging. Andrea is a member Arcadia Association of Realtors, member California Association of Realtors member, and National Association of Realtors. She has been married to her husband Mark for 27 years and they have two wonderful boys, Jordan and Drew.
